<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<!DOCTYPE plist PUBLIC "-//Apple//DTD PLIST 1.0//EN" "http://www.apple.com/DTDs/PropertyList-1.0.dtd">
<plist version="1.0">
<dict>
    <!--
        IKAROS Workspace entitlements.

        2026-04-23: Removed `com.apple.security.app-sandbox`. The app
        is a consultant's professional workspace distributed direct-
        to-consultant (not via App Store), and it legitimately needs:
          - Subprocess exec of `claude`, `npx`, `which` (for the
            binary resolver)
          - Reads outside the app container (user's vault at
            `~/.ikrs-workspace/vaults/`, node_modules discovery,
            nvm paths for MCP servers)
          - Writes to the user's real home for per-engagement vaults

        Under app-sandbox all of the above requires a specific
        temporary-exception entitlement. Moe saw:
          - "Claude CLI not found" — binary_resolver blocked from
            spawning `which` and reading `~/.nvm/...`
          - "Failed to create MCP tmp file at 0600: EPERM" —
            mcp_config blocked from writing to engagement's vault
          - "Path outside allowed vault directory" — skills
            validator saw a canonical path outside the sandbox's
            idea of the container
        All three are resolved by dropping app-sandbox.

        Hardened Runtime (required for future notarization) is
        independent of sandbox — the cs.* opt-outs below handle it.
    -->

    <!-- Hardened Runtime opt-outs that Tauri + WebKit need. -->
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-jit</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-unsigned-executable-memory</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.allow-dyld-environment-variables</key>
    <true/>
    <key>com.apple.security.cs.disable-library-validation</key>
    <true/>
</dict>
</plist>
